==English==
===Noun===
'''trapezium''' (''plural'' '''trapeziums''' or '''trapezia''')

# (''geometry'') (''British'') A four-sided [[polygon]] with exactly two parallel sides (called a [[trapezoid]] in British English).
# (''geometry'') (''US'') A four-sided [[polygon]] with no two sides parallel (known as a [[trapezoid]] in US English).
#A bone of the carpus at the base of the first metacarpal, or thumb.
#A region on the ventral side of the brain, either just back of the pons Varolii, or, as in man, covered by the posterior extension of its transverse fibers.

